==English==
'''Jahbulon''' is a name '''[[wikipedia:York Rite| York Rite Freemasons]]''' used to substitute an [[ineffable]] name of [[wikipedia:Yahwe|the God of Israel]].

===Etymology===
Among [[wikipedia:Freemasons|Freemasons]] it is explained as being a combination of:-
*'''Jah''', a purposely abbreviated version of '''[[wikipedia:Tetragrammaton|YHWY]]'''.
*'''bul''', a form of [[wikipedia:Baal|Baal]].
*'''on''', explained as a name of the [[wikipedia:Ancient Egypt|Egyptian]] god [[wikipedia:Osiris|Osiris]].

==speculative Etymology== 
* It is distinctly possible that the "on" of this word arose by misunderstanding [[wikipedia:Genesis|Osiris]] 46:20 ([[Bible]]): ".. Potiphera priest of On ...", where '''On''' is a version of the[[wikipedia:Ancient Egyptian|Ancient Egyptian]] name of the city of [[wikipedia:Heliopolis|Heliopolis]].
*'''Jahbulon''' may have  arisen as a mixture of [[Jah]] (a [[wikipedia:Hebrew language|Hebrew]] name of God) and [[wikipedia:Zebulon|Zebulon]] (a son of [[wikipedia:Jacob|Jacob]]).

Among Freemasons, this name should only be pronounced with certain rituals.